; Of course, Gorbachev initiated those changes, and history will credit him for that. ; Yeltsin had two talents that Gorbachev lacked. But almost certainly the failure of the counterrevolution will accelerate the democratic revolution it tried to choke. ; But the people of the Soviet Union apparently concluded that the real issue was not Gorbachev himself, but the new political culture of freedom and even democracy that his reforms had created. They thought the issue was Mikhail Gorbachev, and apparently believed that by neutralizing Gorbachev and threatening everyone else, they could quickly take charge of the country. 